"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-10-China-s-queen-of-the-beam-Deng-Linlin-shares-Olympic-experience-1v7EPZiSgSs-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  \\\"Hey Champ!\\\" is a special series by CGTN for Paris 2024, where CGTN invites Olympic champions from all disciplines to visit schools and local communities in China, have some fun with sports enthusiasts and reflect on their Olympic experience.  In this episode, CGTN takes two-time Olympic gold medalist in gymnastics Deng Linlin to Zheshan Park in Wuhu, east China's Anhui Province, on a weekday morning. How do locals exercise in the morning? Did they impress China's \\\"queen of the beam\\\"? After over a decade, how does Deng recall her Olympic experience? Let us find out.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"